author: woolfel
msg: refactored a bit and made it so the sampler only checks if JMeter
was started in NonGui mode. In Gui mode it doesn't make sense to
automatically override the proxy that is already in the test plan.
peter lin

author: woolfel
msg: When JMeter is started in NonGui mode, it now sets System
properties, so samplers can pick it up. Without this, it was a
bit tricky to figure when webservice sampler should use
proxy.

author: woolfel
msg: updated the sampler to check the system properties to see if the
user passed proxy host and port from command line. if the proxy
host and port were not explicitly provided in the test plan, but it
was passed in command line, the sampler will now pick up those
values and use them.
peter lin
